    "icd11_source": "WHO ICD-11 MMS 2024 release — https://icd.who.int/browse11/l-m/en",
    "verification_note": "Entries with `verify: true` should be confirmed in the ICD-11 browser before clinical reliance. Dual coding lets the app fall back to MedlinePlus (US, ICD-10-based) when ICD-11 has no patient-education resource, while exposing diagnoses like c-PTSD that ICD-10 / DSM-5 do not recognize.",
    "changelog": {
      "v2 (2026-06-16)": [
        "Dual coding (icd10 + icd11) on every entry",
        "EDS subtype codes CORRECTED: hEDS Q79.62, vEDS Q79.63, clEDS Q79.69 (was incorrectly assigned in v1)",
        "clEDS label fixed: 'clásico-like (TNXB)' (was 'clásico' — clinically different from classical EDS)",
        "Added separate entry for classical EDS (COL5A1/A2) at Q79.61",
        "17 new EDS-related comorbidities added",
        "Tiroiditis de Hashimoto added as autoimmune adjacency"
      ],
      "v1": "Initial release with 38 entries, ICD-10-CM only, EDS subtype codes swapped"
    }
  },
